1
00:00:06,173 --> 00:00:08,926
GIMLI: It's true, you don't see
many Dwarf women.

2
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:12,763
And in fact, they are so alike
in voice and appearance...

3
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:16,141
...that they're often mistaken
for Dwarf men.

4
00:00:16,475 --> 00:00:18,393
It's the beards.

5
00:00:18,644 --> 00:00:20,729
This, in turn, has given rise
to the belief...

6
00:00:20,896 --> 00:00:23,774
...that there are no Dwarf women...

7
00:00:23,941 --> 00:00:28,195
...and that Dwarves just spring out
of holes in the ground...

8
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:31,240
...which is, of course, ridiculous.

9
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:32,866
[YELLS]

10
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:40,165
GIMLI:
It's all right. Nobody panic.

11
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:42,543
That was deliberate.
It was deliberate.

12
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:48,298
I haven't seen my niece smile
for a long time.

13
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:51,343
She was a girl when they brought
her father back dead.

14
00:00:51,510 --> 00:00:53,804
Cut down by Orcs.

15
00:00:53,971 --> 00:00:56,974
She watched her mother
succumb to grief.

16
00:00:57,599 --> 00:01:02,312
Then she was left alone,
to tend her king in growing fear.

17
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:07,025
Doomed to wait upon an old man,
who should have loved her as a father.

18
00:01:16,994 --> 00:01:19,371
Gimli.

19
00:01:19,538 --> 00:01:21,623
No, I couldn't.

20
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:23,625
I really couldn't.

21
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:29,756
I made some stew.

22
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:33,218
It isn't much, but it's hot.

23
00:01:41,018 --> 00:01:43,061
Thank you.

24
00:02:03,582 --> 00:02:06,126
-It's good.
-Really?

25
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:13,467
My uncle told me a strange thing.

26
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:18,847
He said that you rode to war
with Thengel, my grandfather.

27
00:02:19,264 --> 00:02:21,767
But he must be mistaken.

28
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:26,396
King Théoden has a good memory.
He was only a small child at the time.

29
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:30,776
Then you must be at least 60.

30
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,404
Seventy?

31
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,490
But you cannot be 80!

32
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:41,203
Eighty-seven.

33
00:02:44,289 --> 00:02:46,416
You are one of the Dúnedain.

34
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:50,587
A descendant of Númenor,
blessed with long life.

35
00:02:51,797 --> 00:02:54,424
It was said that your race
had passed into legend.

36
00:02:55,092 --> 00:02:56,843
There are few of us left.

37
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:59,846
The Northern Kingdom
was destroyed long ago.

38
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:04,017
I'm sorry. Please, eat.

39
00:03:18,657 --> 00:03:22,828
ARWEN: <i> The light of the Evenstar
does not wax and wane.</i>

40
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:27,040
<i>It is mine to give to whom I will.</i>

41
00:03:28,834 --> 00:03:31,253
<i>Like my heart.</i>

42
00:03:32,671 --> 00:03:35,382
<i>Go to sleep.</i>

43
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:38,051
I am asleep.

44
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:46,476
This is a dream.

45
00:03:48,687 --> 00:03:51,898
Then it is a good dream.

46
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:05,996
Sleep.

47
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:32,656
[IN SINDARIN] (Minlû pedich nin...)

48
00:04:35,047 --> 00:04:37,303
(i aur hen telitha.)

49
00:04:38,273 --> 00:04:41,066
(Ú i vethed... nâ i onnad.)

50
00:04:41,091 --> 00:04:43,251
(Boe bedich go Frodo.)

51
00:04:43,926 --> 00:04:46,105
(Han bâd lîn.)

52
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:59,175
(Dolen i vâd o nin.)

53
00:04:59,834 --> 00:05:03,529
(Si peliannen i vâd na dail lîn.)

54
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:06,909
(Si boe ú-dhannathach.)

55
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:10,894
Arwen...

56
00:05:13,414 --> 00:05:15,711
(Ae ú-esteliach nad...)

57
00:05:16,086 --> 00:05:18,163
(estelio han...)

58
00:05:19,335 --> 00:05:21,419
(estelio ammen.)

59
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,195
ÉOWYN:
Where is she?

60
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:05,782
The woman who gave you that jewel.

61
00:06:09,119 --> 00:06:11,872
ELROND:
<i>Our time here is ending.</i>

62
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:15,125
Arwen's time is ending.

63
00:06:15,834 --> 00:06:17,127
Let her go.

64
00:06:17,294 --> 00:06:19,296
Let her take the ship into the west.

65
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:22,549
Let her bear away her love for you
to the Undying Lands.

66
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:24,509
There it will be ever green.

67
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:28,388
But never more than memory.

68
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:32,684
I will not leave my daughter here
to die.

69
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:36,521
-She stays because she still has hope.
-She stays for you.

70
00:06:36,688 --> 00:06:39,024
She belongs with her people.

71
00:06:51,394 --> 00:06:54,465
[IN SINDARIN] (Nach gwannatha sin?)

72
00:06:54,490 --> 00:06:57,803
(Ma nathach hi gwannathach or minuial - archened?)

73
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:02,942
[IN SINDARIN] (Ú-ethelithon.)

74
00:07:03,745 --> 00:07:05,733
(Estelio guru lîn ne dagor.)

75
00:07:05,757 --> 00:07:07,318
(Ethelithach.)

76
00:07:07,342 --> 00:07:09,565
(Ú-bedin o gurth ne dagor.)

77
00:07:09,589 --> 00:07:12,075
(O man pedich?)

78
00:07:17,037 --> 00:07:19,037
(Edra le men...)

79
00:07:19,163 --> 00:07:20,420
(...men na guil edwen...)

80
00:07:22,215 --> 00:07:26,839
(haer o auth...a nîr...a naeth.)

81
00:07:27,322 --> 00:07:29,157
[IN ENGLISH]
Why are you saying this?

82
00:07:30,742 --> 00:07:33,912
[IN ENGLISH]
I am mortal. You are Elf-kind.

83
00:07:35,372 --> 00:07:38,041
It was a dream, Arwen.

84
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,834
Nothing more.

85
00:07:41,211 --> 00:07:44,422
I don't believe you.

86
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:55,266
This belongs to you.

87
00:07:58,019 --> 00:07:59,604
It was a gift.

88
00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:03,775
Keep it.

89
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:07,487
ÉOWYN:
My lord?

90
00:08:10,281 --> 00:08:14,869
She is sailing to the Undying Lands
with all that is left of her kin.

91
00:08:36,558 --> 00:08:37,851
[HORSE NEIGHS]

92
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:39,811
What is it?

93
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:43,356
-Háma?
-I'm not sure.

94
00:08:48,987 --> 00:08:51,823
[YELLING AND ROARING]

95
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:02,000
Wargs!

96
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:16,181
A scout!

97
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:25,023
-What is it? What do you see?
-Warg! We're under attack!

98
00:09:26,357 --> 00:09:28,568
Get them out of here!

99
00:09:33,323 --> 00:09:35,366
All riders to the head of the column.

100
00:09:36,034 --> 00:09:38,036
GIMLI:
Come on. Get me up here. I'm a rider.

101
00:09:38,203 --> 00:09:39,954
Come on!

102
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:45,126
[WARGS BARKING]

103
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:54,219
You must lead the people
to Helm's Deep, and make haste.

104
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:55,887
-I can fight.
-No!

105
00:09:58,556 --> 00:10:00,642
You must do this, for me.

106
00:10:02,644 --> 00:10:04,229
Follow me! Hyah!

107
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:12,070
GIMLI: Forward. I mean, charge forward.
ÉOWYN: Make for the lower ground!

108
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:14,906
-That's it! Go on!
-Stay together!

109
00:11:27,145 --> 00:11:29,439
GIMLI:
Bring your pretty face to my ax.

110
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:33,818
That one counts as mine!

111
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:52,128
Stinking creature.

112
00:11:57,217 --> 00:11:58,843
[SNIFFS]

113
00:12:02,138 --> 00:12:04,182
[GRUNTING]

114
00:13:04,075 --> 00:13:05,493
[YELLS]

115
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:21,259
Aragorn!

116
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:27,432
Aragorn?

117
00:13:33,271 --> 00:13:36,024
[LAUGHING]

118
00:13:41,446 --> 00:13:44,365
Tell me what happened
and I will ease your passing.

119
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:45,950
He's...

120
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:48,119
...dead.

121
00:13:48,786 --> 00:13:51,664
He took a little tumble off the cliff.

122
00:13:55,293 --> 00:13:56,586
You lie.

123
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:59,505
[CHOKES]

124
00:14:30,495 --> 00:14:32,121
Get the wounded on horses.

125
00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:36,584
The wolves of Isengard will return.

126
00:14:37,001 --> 00:14:39,128
Leave the dead.

127
00:14:46,511 --> 00:14:48,012
Come.

128
00:14:58,189 --> 00:14:59,816
WOMAN 1: At last!
WOMAN 2: Helm's Deep.

129
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:02,860
WOMAN 3:
There it is, Helm's Deep.

130
00:15:05,405 --> 00:15:07,240
WOMAN 4:
We're safe!

131
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:11,619
We're safe, my lady.

132
00:15:11,786 --> 00:15:12,995
Thank you.

133
00:15:57,331 --> 00:15:58,749
FREDA: Mama!
MORWEN: Éothain!

134
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,460
Freda!

135
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:09,051
-Where is the rest?
-This is all we could save, my lady.

136
00:16:12,889 --> 00:16:14,223
Take it to the caves.

137
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:17,226
MAN:
Make way for the king.

138
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:22,064
GAMLING: Make way for Théoden.
Make way for the king.

139
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:33,701
So few. So few of you have returned.

140
00:16:36,454 --> 00:16:38,748
Our people are safe.

141
00:16:40,082 --> 00:16:42,627
We have paid for it with many lives.

142
00:16:43,461 --> 00:16:45,004
GIMLI:
My lady.

143
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:50,968
Lord Aragorn...

144
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:52,386
...where is he?

145
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:55,932
He fell.

146
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:21,582
Draw all our forces behind the wall.

147
00:17:21,749 --> 00:17:24,669
Bar the gate.
And set a watch on the surround.

148
00:17:24,919 --> 00:17:28,005
GAMLING: What of those who cannot
fight, my lord? The women and children?

149
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:30,800
THÉODEN:
Get them into the caves.

150
00:17:31,676 --> 00:17:36,514
Saruman's arm will have grown long
indeed if he thinks he can reach us here.

151
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:41,978
WORMTONGUE:
<i>Helm's Deep has one weakness.</i>

152
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:44,480
<i>Its outer wall is solid rock...</i>

153
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:47,733
<i>...but for a small culvert
at its base...</i>

154
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,695
<i>...which is little more than a drain.</i>

155
00:17:53,531 --> 00:17:57,702
How? How can fire undo stone?

156
00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:02,415
What kind of device
could bring down the wall?

157
00:18:06,043 --> 00:18:10,047
SARUMAN: If the wall is breached,
Helm's Deep will fall.

158
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:13,718
Even if it is breached, it would take
a number beyond reckoning...

159
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:16,470
...thousands, to storm the Keep.

160
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:18,055
SARUMAN:
Tens of thousands.

161
00:18:18,222 --> 00:18:22,310
WORMTONGUE:
But, my lord, there is no such force.

162
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:24,270
[HORNS SOUNDING]

163
00:18:24,336 --> 00:18:26,110
[URUK-HAI CHANTING IN BLACK SPEECH]: <i>Lord of the Ring!
(Durbgu nazgshu!)</i>

164
00:18:26,134 --> 00:18:27,908
<i>Lord of the Earth!
(Durbgu dashshu!)</i>

165
00:18:28,491 --> 00:18:30,265
<i>Lord of the Ring!
(Durbgu nazgshu!)</i>

166
00:18:30,735 --> 00:18:32,509
<i>Lord of the Earth!
(Durbgu dashshu!)</i>

167
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:37,325
A new power is rising.

168
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:40,494
Its victory is at hand.

169
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:48,252
This night...

170
00:18:48,669 --> 00:18:53,007
...the land will be stained
with the blood of Rohan!

171
00:18:53,174 --> 00:18:56,510
March to Helm's Deep!

172
00:18:56,677 --> 00:19:00,181
Leave none alive!

173
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:05,186
To war!

174
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:13,569
There will be no dawn for Men.

175
00:19:30,753 --> 00:19:32,797
Look. There's smoke to the south.

176
00:19:32,963 --> 00:19:36,133
There is always smoke rising...

177
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:40,179
...from Isengard these days.

178
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:42,014
Isengard?

179
00:19:42,223 --> 00:19:44,100
TREEBEARD:
There was a time...

180
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:47,978
...when Saruman would walk in my woods.

181
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:51,482
But now he has a mind of metal...

182
00:19:52,149 --> 00:19:54,610
...and wheels.

183
00:19:55,361 --> 00:19:59,865
He no longer cares for growing things.

184
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:01,826
What is it?

185
00:20:06,831 --> 00:20:09,041
It's Saruman's army.

186
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:10,793
The war has started.

187
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:53,461
ARWEN: <i> May the grace of the Valar
protect you.</i>

188
00:21:25,743 --> 00:21:27,620
Brego.

189
00:21:53,729 --> 00:21:54,897
ELROND:
Arwen.

190
00:21:56,198 --> 00:21:58,152
[IN SINDARIN] (Tollen i lû.)

191
00:22:00,159 --> 00:22:04,081
(I chair gwannar na Valannor. Si bado... no círar.)

192
00:22:04,782 --> 00:22:06,575
I have made my choice.

193
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:15,876
[IN ENGLISH]
He is not coming back.

194
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:20,631
Why do you linger here
when there is no hope?

195
00:22:21,549 --> 00:22:24,552
There is still hope.

196
00:22:28,681 --> 00:22:32,476
If Aragorn survives this war,
you will still be parted.

197
00:22:35,855 --> 00:22:38,816
If Sauron is defeated
and Aragorn made king...

198
00:22:38,983 --> 00:22:41,485
...and all that you hope for
comes true...

199
00:22:41,652 --> 00:22:46,365
...you will still have to taste
the bitterness of mortality.

200
00:22:46,657 --> 00:22:49,660
Whether by the sword
or the slow decay of time...

201
00:22:49,827 --> 00:22:52,746
...Aragorn will die.

202
00:22:55,583 --> 00:22:58,168
<i>And there will be no comfort
for you...</i>

203
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:02,548
<i>...no comfort to ease the pain
of his passing.</i>

204
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:08,095
<i>He will come to death...</i>

205
00:23:08,262 --> 00:23:10,848
<i>...an image of the splendor
of the kings of Men...</i>

206
00:23:11,015 --> 00:23:15,686
<i>...in glory undimmed before
the breaking of the world.</i>

207
00:23:24,778 --> 00:23:28,741
<i>But you, my daughter...</i>

208
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:34,580
<i>...you will linger on in darkness
and in doubt...</i>

209
00:23:34,747 --> 00:23:38,834
<i>...as nightfall in winter
that comes without a star.</i>

210
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:43,631
<i>Here you will dwell...</i>

211
00:23:43,797 --> 00:23:48,719
<i>...bound to your grief
under the fading trees...</i>

212
00:23:50,429 --> 00:23:52,431
<i>...until all the world is changed...</i>

213
00:23:52,598 --> 00:23:57,102
...and the long years of your life
are utterly spent.

214
00:24:05,653 --> 00:24:06,820
Arwen.

215
00:24:13,452 --> 00:24:15,746
There is nothing for you here...

216
00:24:16,413 --> 00:24:18,499
...only death.

217
00:24:39,269 --> 00:24:42,458
[IN SINDARIN] (A im ú-'erin veleth lîn?)

218
00:24:44,029 --> 00:24:45,794
(Gerich meleth nîn, ada.)

219
00:25:37,036 --> 00:25:40,205
GALADRIEL [IN SINDARIN]: <i> The world is changed.
(I amar prestar aen.)</i>

220
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:42,767
I feel it in the water,
(Han mathon ne nen,)

221
00:25:43,169 --> 00:25:45,169
I feel it in the earth,
(han mathon ne chae,)

222
00:25:46,941 --> 00:25:49,164
and I smell it in...
(a han noston ned...)

223
00:25:50,012 --> 00:25:51,265
...the air.
(...'wilith.)

224
00:25:51,925 --> 00:25:55,554
[IN ENGLISH]:
<i>The power of the enemy is growing.</i>

225
00:25:55,721 --> 00:25:58,348
<i>Sauron will use his puppet,
Saruman...</i>

226
00:25:58,515 --> 00:26:01,977
<i>...to destroy the people of Rohan.</i>

227
00:26:04,021 --> 00:26:07,691
<i>Isengard has been unleashed.</i>

228
00:26:11,987 --> 00:26:15,365
<i>The Eye of Sauron now turns
to Gondor...</i>

229
00:26:16,492 --> 00:26:19,495
<i>...the last free kingdom of Men.</i>

230
00:26:19,661 --> 00:26:24,041
<i>His war on this country
will come swiftly.</i>

231
00:26:27,753 --> 00:26:30,881
<i>He senses the Ring is close.</i>

232
00:26:31,048 --> 00:26:34,510
<i>The strength of the Ring-bearer
is failing.</i>

233
00:26:34,676 --> 00:26:38,722
<i>In his heart, Frodo begins
to understand...</i>

234
00:26:40,265 --> 00:26:44,144
...the quest will claim his life.

235
00:26:44,311 --> 00:26:46,480
You know this.

236
00:26:47,064 --> 00:26:49,900
<i>You have foreseen it.</i>

237
00:26:52,027 --> 00:26:55,489
<i>It is the risk we all took.</i>

238
00:26:59,868 --> 00:27:04,081
<i>In the gathering dark, the will
of the Ring grows strong.</i>

239
00:27:05,249 --> 00:27:09,670
<i>It works hard now to find its way back
into the hands of Men.</i>

240
00:27:09,837 --> 00:27:15,300
<i>Men, who are so easily seduced
by its power.</i>

241
00:27:15,509 --> 00:27:19,096
<i>The young captain of Gondor
has but to extend his hand...</i>

242
00:27:19,263 --> 00:27:23,350
<i>...take the Ring for his own,
and the world will fall.</i>

243
00:27:25,769 --> 00:27:27,604
<i>It is close now.</i>

244
00:27:27,771 --> 00:27:32,025
<i>So close to achieving its goal.</i>

245
00:27:32,901 --> 00:27:34,820
[ROARING]

246
00:27:35,112 --> 00:27:38,782
<i>For Sauron will have dominion
over all life on this Earth...</i>

247
00:27:38,949 --> 00:27:43,078
<i>...even unto the ending
of the world.</i>

248
00:27:44,913 --> 00:27:46,748
<i>The time of the Elves...</i>

249
00:27:46,957 --> 00:27:48,876
<i>...is over.</i>

250
00:27:49,710 --> 00:27:53,297
<i>Do we leave Middle-earth
to its fate?</i>

251
00:27:55,257 --> 00:27:58,510
<i>Do we let them stand alone?</i>

252
00:28:03,140 --> 00:28:04,474
What news?

253
00:28:04,641 --> 00:28:07,477
Our scouts report Saruman
has attacked Rohan.

254
00:28:07,644 --> 00:28:10,480
Théoden's people have fled
to Helm's Deep.

255
00:28:10,647 --> 00:28:14,693
But we must look to our own borders.
Faramir, Orcs are on the move.

256
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:17,279
Sauron is marshaling an army.

257
00:28:17,613 --> 00:28:19,740
Easterlings and Southrons
are at the Black Gate.

258
00:28:19,907 --> 00:28:23,327
-How many?
-Some thousands. More come every day.

259
00:28:24,411 --> 00:28:27,998
-Who's covering the river to the north?
-We pulled 500 men at Osgiliath.

260
00:28:28,165 --> 00:28:31,210
If their city is attacked,
we won't hold it.

261
00:28:33,337 --> 00:28:35,505
FARAMIR:
Saruman attacks from Isengard.

262
00:28:35,672 --> 00:28:38,383
Sauron from Mordor.

263
00:28:39,676 --> 00:28:42,930
The fight will come to Men
on both fronts.

264
00:28:43,096 --> 00:28:44,806
Gondor is weak.

265
00:28:44,973 --> 00:28:48,101
Sauron will strike us soon.

266
00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:50,687
And he will strike hard.

267
00:28:51,146 --> 00:28:55,234
He knows now we do not have
the strength to repel him.

268
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:11,375
My men tell me that you are Orc spies.

269
00:29:11,541 --> 00:29:14,294
Spies? Now wait just a minute.

270
00:29:14,461 --> 00:29:16,713
Well, if you're not spies,
then who are you?

271
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:25,347
Speak.

272
00:29:26,431 --> 00:29:29,059
We are Hobbits of the Shire.

273
00:29:29,393 --> 00:29:32,396
Frodo Baggins is my name,
and this is Samwise Gamgee.

274
00:29:32,813 --> 00:29:34,356
Your bodyguard?

275
00:29:34,523 --> 00:29:36,316
His gardener.

276
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:38,902
And where is your skulking friend?

277
00:29:40,404 --> 00:29:42,739
That gangrel creature.

278
00:29:43,073 --> 00:29:45,033
He had an ill-favored look.

279
00:29:46,743 --> 00:29:48,662
There was no other.

280
00:29:52,749 --> 00:29:55,085
We set out from Rivendell
with seven companions.

281
00:29:58,422 --> 00:30:01,508
One we lost in Moria...

282
00:30:02,592 --> 00:30:04,094
...two were my kin...

283
00:30:04,261 --> 00:30:08,015
...a Dwarf there was also.
And an Elf and two Men.

284
00:30:08,181 --> 00:30:12,102
Aragorn, son of Arathorn,
and Boromir of Gondor.

285
00:30:17,107 --> 00:30:18,859
You're a friend of Boromir?

286
00:30:21,278 --> 00:30:22,779
Yes.

287
00:30:23,864 --> 00:30:24,948
For my part.

288
00:30:31,455 --> 00:30:34,416
It will grieve you then to learn
that he is dead.

289
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:37,919
Dead?

290
00:30:38,086 --> 00:30:40,130
How? When?

291
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:43,050
As one of his companions,
I'd hoped you would tell me.

292
00:30:43,342 --> 00:30:47,179
If something has happened to Boromir,
we would have you tell us.

293
00:30:49,931 --> 00:30:56,396
His horn washed up upon the riverbank,
about six days past.

294
00:30:56,605 --> 00:30:59,691
It was cloven in two.

295
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:04,780
But more than this, I know it in my heart.

296
00:31:06,823 --> 00:31:08,617
He was my brother.

297
00:31:55,330 --> 00:31:57,332
[MEN CHEERING]

298
00:31:57,499 --> 00:32:00,544
MEN:
Boromir!

299
00:32:01,044 --> 00:32:02,921
Boromir!

300
00:32:07,175 --> 00:32:10,929
This city was once the jewel
of our kingdom.

301
00:32:11,096 --> 00:32:14,766
A place of light and beauty and music.

302
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:17,269
And so it shall be once more!

303
00:32:19,813 --> 00:32:22,482
Let the armies of Mordor know this:

304
00:32:22,649 --> 00:32:27,028
Never again will the land of my people
fall into enemy hands.

305
00:32:30,824 --> 00:32:36,496
This city of Osgiliath
has been reclaimed for Gondor!

306
00:32:36,872 --> 00:32:38,832
-For Gondor!
-For Gondor!

307
00:32:38,999 --> 00:32:41,835
-For Gondor!
-For Gondor!

308
00:32:50,552 --> 00:32:53,305
Good speech. Nice and short.

309
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:56,391
Leaves more time for drinking!

310
00:32:56,683 --> 00:33:00,937
Break out the ale! These men are thirsty!

311
00:33:04,399 --> 00:33:06,568
Remember today, little brother.

312
00:33:06,735 --> 00:33:09,738
Today, life is good.

313
00:33:13,909 --> 00:33:15,494
What?

314
00:33:15,869 --> 00:33:17,329
He's here.

315
00:33:20,540 --> 00:33:23,585
-Moment of peace, can he not give us that?
DENETHOR: Where is he?

316
00:33:23,752 --> 00:33:27,214
Where is Gondor's finest?
Where's my first-born?

317
00:33:27,756 --> 00:33:29,466
Father!

318
00:33:34,304 --> 00:33:36,681
They say you vanquished the enemy
almost single-handedly.

319
00:33:36,848 --> 00:33:40,268
They exaggerate.
The victory belongs to Faramir also.

320
00:33:41,728 --> 00:33:44,648
But for Faramir, this city
would still be standing.

321
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:47,734
Were you not entrusted to protect it?

322
00:33:47,901 --> 00:33:49,945
I would have done,
but our numbers were too few.

323
00:33:50,111 --> 00:33:51,821
Oh, too few.

324
00:33:52,322 --> 00:33:54,699
You let the enemy walk in
and take it on a whim.

325
00:33:56,910 --> 00:33:59,996
Always you cast a poor reflection on me.

326
00:34:00,163 --> 00:34:02,415
That is not my intent.

327
00:34:02,582 --> 00:34:06,336
You give him no credit,
and yet he tries to do your will.

328
00:34:09,714 --> 00:34:12,634
-He loves you, Father.
-Do not trouble me with Faramir...

329
00:34:12,801 --> 00:34:15,554
...I know his uses, and they are few.

330
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:19,349
We have more urgent things to speak of.

331
00:34:20,517 --> 00:34:22,936
Elrond of Rivendell has called a meeting.

332
00:34:23,103 --> 00:34:25,981
He will not say why,
but I have guessed its purpose.

333
00:34:26,147 --> 00:34:29,943
It is rumored that the weapon
of the enemy has been found.

334
00:34:32,153 --> 00:34:34,447
The One Ring.

335
00:34:37,200 --> 00:34:41,871
-Isildur's Bane.
-It has fallen into the hands of the Elves.

336
00:34:42,038 --> 00:34:45,667
Everyone will try to claim it:
Men, Dwarves, wizards.

337
00:34:45,834 --> 00:34:49,963
We cannot let that happen.
This thing must come to Gondor.

338
00:34:51,756 --> 00:34:54,426
-Gondor.
-It's dangerous, I know.

339
00:34:54,593 --> 00:34:58,305
Ever the Ring will seek to corrupt
the hearts of lesser Men.

340
00:34:58,471 --> 00:35:02,434
But you, you are strong.
And our need is great.

341
00:35:02,601 --> 00:35:07,897
It is our blood which is being spilled,
our people who are dying.

342
00:35:08,064 --> 00:35:13,153
Sauron is biding his time.
He's massing fresh armies.

343
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:14,821
He will return.

344
00:35:14,988 --> 00:35:18,742
And when he does,
we will be powerless to stop him.

345
00:35:18,908 --> 00:35:21,453
You must go.

346
00:35:22,621 --> 00:35:24,748
Bring me back this mighty gift.

347
00:35:25,582 --> 00:35:31,087
No. My place is here with my people.
Not in Rivendell.

348
00:35:31,254 --> 00:35:34,924
-Would you deny your own father?
-If there is need to go to Rivendell...

349
00:35:35,091 --> 00:35:38,094
-...send me in his stead.
-You?

350
00:35:39,262 --> 00:35:41,181
Oh, I see.

351
00:35:41,348 --> 00:35:45,560
A chance for Faramir, captain of Gondor,
to show his quality.

352
00:35:45,977 --> 00:35:47,979
I think not.

353
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:51,024
I trust this mission only to your brother.

354
00:35:51,191 --> 00:35:54,110
The one who will not fail me.

355
00:36:11,252 --> 00:36:14,422
Remember today, little brother.

356
00:36:32,774 --> 00:36:34,776
MAN:
Captain Faramir!

357
00:36:36,027 --> 00:36:38,154
[WHISPERING]
We found the third one.

358
00:36:43,743 --> 00:36:45,578
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

359
00:36:49,666 --> 00:36:51,668
You must come with me. Now.

360
00:37:02,887 --> 00:37:04,013
Down there.

361
00:37:18,903 --> 00:37:21,781
To enter the Forbidden Pool
bears the penalty of death.

362
00:37:32,375 --> 00:37:33,877
They wait for my command.

363
00:37:39,382 --> 00:37:40,467
Shall I shoot?

364
00:37:41,718 --> 00:37:44,721
<i>The rock and pool
Is nice and cool</i>

365
00:37:44,888 --> 00:37:46,723
<i>So juicy sweet</i>

366
00:37:47,390 --> 00:37:50,351
<i>Our only wish
To catch a fish</i>

367
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:53,229
<i>So juicy sweet</i>

368
00:37:56,691 --> 00:37:58,401
[YELLS]

369
00:38:00,236 --> 00:38:01,613
Wait.

370
00:38:03,114 --> 00:38:05,950
This creature is bound to me.

371
00:38:06,576 --> 00:38:08,495
And I to him.

372
00:38:11,748 --> 00:38:13,082
He is our guide.

373
00:38:17,796 --> 00:38:19,214
Please...

374
00:38:19,380 --> 00:38:21,257
...let me go down to him.

375
00:38:32,519 --> 00:38:34,187
Sméagol.

376
00:38:35,188 --> 00:38:37,440
Master is here.

377
00:38:38,608 --> 00:38:39,776
Come, Sméagol.

378
00:38:42,612 --> 00:38:45,281
Trust master. Come.

379
00:38:48,451 --> 00:38:52,288
We must go now?

380
00:38:52,622 --> 00:38:56,084
Sméagol, you must trust master.

381
00:38:56,251 --> 00:38:57,627
Follow me. Come on.

382
00:38:58,837 --> 00:39:00,463
Come.

383
00:39:02,966 --> 00:39:04,133
Come, Sméagol.

384
00:39:04,634 --> 00:39:06,719
Nice Sméagol. That's it.

385
00:39:07,220 --> 00:39:08,763
Come on.

386
00:39:10,598 --> 00:39:11,850
[FOOTSTEP]

387
00:39:13,142 --> 00:39:14,811
Don't hurt him!

388
00:39:14,978 --> 00:39:17,730
Sméagol, don't struggle.
Sméagol, listen to me.

389
00:39:17,897 --> 00:39:19,190
Master!

390
00:39:22,277 --> 00:39:24,654
[MUFFLED CRIES]

391
00:39:30,285 --> 00:39:33,997
[GRUNTING AND PANTING]

392
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:46,759
That's enough.

393
00:39:50,388 --> 00:39:52,557
Where are you leading them?

394
00:39:52,724 --> 00:39:54,142
[CRYING]

395
00:39:54,350 --> 00:39:56,019
FARAMIR:
Answer me.

396
00:39:56,853 --> 00:40:00,064
GOLLUM:
Sméagol.

397
00:40:00,398 --> 00:40:02,609
[CRYING]

398
00:40:03,526 --> 00:40:08,281
GOLLUM:
Why does it cry, Sméagol?

399
00:40:09,532 --> 00:40:12,160
SMÉAGOL:
Cruel Men hurts us.

400
00:40:12,327 --> 00:40:15,330
Master tricksed us.

401
00:40:15,496 --> 00:40:19,042
GOLLUM:
Of course he did.

402
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:23,129
I told you he was tricksy.

403
00:40:23,296 --> 00:40:26,341
I told you he was false.

404
00:40:26,507 --> 00:40:29,218
SMÉAGOL:
Master is our friend.

405
00:40:29,385 --> 00:40:31,721
Our friend.

406
00:40:31,888 --> 00:40:34,057
GOLLUM:
Master betrayed us.

407
00:40:34,223 --> 00:40:37,226
SMÉAGOL:
No. Not its business.

408
00:40:38,311 --> 00:40:40,730
Leave us alone!

409
00:40:40,897 --> 00:40:43,316
GOLLUM:
Filthy little Hobbitses!

410
00:40:43,483 --> 00:40:45,777
They stole it from us!

411
00:40:45,944 --> 00:40:47,403
SMÉAGOL:
No. No.

412
00:40:47,946 --> 00:40:49,572
What did they steal?

413
00:40:51,741 --> 00:40:57,080
GOLLUM:
My precious!

414
00:40:57,538 --> 00:41:00,083
[YELLS]

415
00:41:00,750 --> 00:41:02,418
We have to get out of here.

416
00:41:03,002 --> 00:41:04,963
You go. Go, now.

417
00:41:07,590 --> 00:41:09,425
You can do it.

418
00:41:10,885 --> 00:41:12,345
Use the Ring, Mr. Frodo.

419
00:41:12,512 --> 00:41:14,305
Just this once.

420
00:41:14,472 --> 00:41:16,265
Put it on.

421
00:41:16,683 --> 00:41:18,726
Disappear.

422
00:41:19,769 --> 00:41:20,853
I can't.

423
00:41:23,940 --> 00:41:26,150
You were right, Sam.

424
00:41:27,610 --> 00:41:30,113
You tried to tell me but...

425
00:41:34,784 --> 00:41:36,953
I'm sorry.

426
00:41:41,499 --> 00:41:44,377
The Ring's taking me, Sam.

427
00:41:45,795 --> 00:41:47,463
If I put it on...

428
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:49,966
...he'll find me.

429
00:41:51,634 --> 00:41:53,594
He'll see.

430
00:41:54,804 --> 00:41:56,806
Mr. Frodo...

431
00:42:01,728 --> 00:42:05,982
So this is the answer
to all the riddles.

432
00:42:08,192 --> 00:42:11,195
Here in the Wild I have you...

433
00:42:11,362 --> 00:42:13,281
...two Halflings...

434
00:42:13,448 --> 00:42:16,617
...and a host of men at my call.

435
00:42:19,912 --> 00:42:23,416
The Ring of Power within my grasp.

436
00:42:33,092 --> 00:42:36,846
A chance for Faramir,
captain of Gondor...

437
00:42:38,431 --> 00:42:41,476
...to show his quality.

438
00:42:58,993 --> 00:43:01,662
[VOICE OF THE RING WHISPERING]

439
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:04,207
No!

440
00:43:07,376 --> 00:43:08,711
Stop it!

441
00:43:08,878 --> 00:43:09,921
Leave him alone.

442
00:43:11,255 --> 00:43:13,758
Don't you understand?

443
00:43:15,051 --> 00:43:16,969
He's got to destroy it!

444
00:43:17,136 --> 00:43:20,389
That's where we're going, into Mordor.

445
00:43:20,556 --> 00:43:22,225
To the Mountain of Fire!

446
00:43:23,267 --> 00:43:26,395
Osgiliath is under attack.
They call for reinforcements.

447
00:43:26,562 --> 00:43:29,565
SAM:
Please. It's such a burden.

448
00:43:31,734 --> 00:43:33,820
Will you not help him?

449
00:43:35,154 --> 00:43:37,073
Captain?

450
00:43:37,740 --> 00:43:39,951
Prepare to leave.

451
00:43:44,914 --> 00:43:47,333
The Ring will go to Gondor.

452
00:43:57,718 --> 00:44:00,972
[DISTANT MARCHING FOOTSTEPS]

453
00:44:47,643 --> 00:44:51,407
[IN SINDARIN] Well done, Brego, my friend.
(Mae carnen, Brego, mellon nîn.)

454
00:45:00,323 --> 00:45:02,992
WOMAN: He's alive!
GIMLI: Where is he? Where is he?

455
00:45:03,159 --> 00:45:06,204
Get out of the way!
I'm going to kill him!

456
00:45:06,370 --> 00:45:10,166
You are the luckiest, the canniest...

457
00:45:10,333 --> 00:45:14,337
...and the most reckless man
I ever knew.

458
00:45:15,004 --> 00:45:16,505
Bless you, laddie.

459
00:45:17,089 --> 00:45:18,841
[IN ENGLISH]
Gimli, where is the king?

460
00:45:27,850 --> 00:45:28,910
[IN SINDARIN] (Le abdollen.)

461
00:45:32,605 --> 00:45:33,940
[IN ENGLISH]
You look terrible.

462
00:46:01,008 --> 00:46:03,844
[IN SINDARIN] Thank you.
(Hannon le.)

463
00:46:09,308 --> 00:46:10,351
[DOORS OPENING]

464
00:46:15,690 --> 00:46:17,733
A great host, you say?

465
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:19,360
[IN ENGLISH]
All Isengard is emptied.

466
00:46:19,527 --> 00:46:20,569
How many?

467
00:46:21,237 --> 00:46:24,240
ARAGORN:
Ten thousand strong at least.

468
00:46:25,783 --> 00:46:27,243
Ten thousand?

469
00:46:27,660 --> 00:46:30,162
It is an army bred for a single purpose:

470
00:46:32,832 --> 00:46:34,959
To destroy the world of Men.

471
00:46:37,461 --> 00:46:39,463
They will be here by nightfall.

472
00:46:45,303 --> 00:46:46,595
Let them come!

473
00:46:48,097 --> 00:46:50,891
I want every man and strong lad
able to bear arms...

474
00:46:51,058 --> 00:46:54,186
...to be ready for battle by nightfall.

475
00:47:02,445 --> 00:47:05,364
We will cover the causeway
and the gate from above.

476
00:47:05,531 --> 00:47:07,950
No army has ever breached
the Deeping Wall...

477
00:47:08,117 --> 00:47:10,870
...or set foot inside the Hornburg!

478
00:47:11,037 --> 00:47:13,456
This is no rabble of mindless Orcs.

479
00:47:14,040 --> 00:47:16,250
These are Uruk-hai.

480
00:47:16,417 --> 00:47:19,837
Their armour is thick
and their shields broad.

481
00:47:21,464 --> 00:47:25,134
I have fought many wars,
Master Dwarf.

482
00:47:25,301 --> 00:47:28,929
I know how to defend my own keep.

483
00:47:35,519 --> 00:47:38,939
They will break upon this fortress
like water on rock.

484
00:47:39,106 --> 00:47:44,320
Saruman's hordes will pillage and burn.
We've seen it before.

485
00:47:44,528 --> 00:47:47,198
Crops can be resown...

486
00:47:47,365 --> 00:47:50,368
...homes rebuilt.

487
00:47:50,993 --> 00:47:53,537
Within these walls...

488
00:47:53,913 --> 00:47:55,414
...we will outlast them.

489
00:47:55,581 --> 00:47:58,000
They do not come to destroy Rohan's
crops or villages.

490
00:47:58,167 --> 00:47:59,710
They come to destroy its people...

491
00:47:59,877 --> 00:48:02,380
...down to the last child.

492
00:48:03,255 --> 00:48:05,508
What would you have me do?

493
00:48:05,674 --> 00:48:07,426
Look at my men.

494
00:48:07,593 --> 00:48:09,345
Their courage hangs by a thread.

495
00:48:11,514 --> 00:48:15,935
If this is to be our end, then I would
have them make such an end...

496
00:48:16,102 --> 00:48:19,146
...as to be worthy of remembrance.

497
00:48:22,775 --> 00:48:24,693
ARAGORN:
Send out riders, my lord.

498
00:48:24,985 --> 00:48:27,863
You must call for aid.

499
00:48:31,117 --> 00:48:33,369
And who will come?

500
00:48:33,786 --> 00:48:35,371
Elves?

501
00:48:35,538 --> 00:48:37,623
Dwarves?

502
00:48:38,374 --> 00:48:41,252
We are not so lucky in our friends
as you.

503
00:48:42,086 --> 00:48:44,380
The old alliances are dead.

504
00:48:44,797 --> 00:48:47,591
-Gondor will answer.
-Gondor?!

505
00:48:47,758 --> 00:48:49,969
Where was Gondor
when the Westfold fell?!

506
00:48:50,928 --> 00:48:54,181
Where was Gondor when
our enemies closed in around us?!

507
00:48:54,348 --> 00:48:56,267
Where was Gon--?

508
00:48:58,936 --> 00:49:00,896
No, my Lord Aragorn...

509
00:49:02,481 --> 00:49:04,942
...we are alone.

510
00:49:11,824 --> 00:49:13,576
Get the women and children
into the caves.

511
00:49:13,742 --> 00:49:14,994
MAN 1: We need more time
to lay provisions--

512
00:49:15,161 --> 00:49:18,664
THÉODEN:
There is no time. War is upon us.

513
00:49:18,914 --> 00:49:20,624
MAN 2:
Secure the gate.

514
00:49:21,292 --> 00:49:24,211
[CAWING]

515
00:49:25,838 --> 00:49:27,923
We Ents have not troubled...

516
00:49:28,132 --> 00:49:31,510
...about the wars of Men and wizards...

517
00:49:32,261 --> 00:49:35,264
...for a very long time.

518
00:49:36,515 --> 00:49:41,270
But now, something
is about to happen...

519
00:49:41,437 --> 00:49:43,772
...that has not happened...

520
00:49:43,981 --> 00:49:46,442
...for an age.

521
00:49:47,651 --> 00:49:49,945
Entmoot.

522
00:49:50,321 --> 00:49:51,363
What's that?

523
00:49:51,780 --> 00:49:54,617
'Tis a gathering.

524
00:49:55,784 --> 00:49:58,370
A gathering of what?

525
00:49:58,662 --> 00:50:01,707
[RUMBLING]

526
00:50:16,305 --> 00:50:18,641
TREEBEARD:
Beech. Oak.

527
00:50:18,807 --> 00:50:20,726
Chestnut. Ash.

528
00:50:20,976 --> 00:50:22,978
Good. Good. Good.

529
00:50:23,145 --> 00:50:25,481
Many have come.

530
00:50:33,030 --> 00:50:35,824
Now we must decide
if the Ents...

531
00:50:35,991 --> 00:50:38,536
...will go to war.

532
00:50:47,503 --> 00:50:50,548
GUARD 1:
Move back! Move to the caves!

533
00:50:53,008 --> 00:50:55,094
GUARD 2:
Come on, people! Quickly, now!

534
00:50:55,511 --> 00:50:57,805
We'll place the reserves along the wall.

535
00:50:57,972 --> 00:51:00,266
They can support the archers
from above the gate.

536
00:51:00,432 --> 00:51:03,561
Aragorn, you must rest.

537
00:51:03,727 --> 00:51:05,229
You're no use to us half alive.

538
00:51:05,396 --> 00:51:06,438
[BABY CRYING]

539
00:51:06,605 --> 00:51:07,815
ÉOWYN:
Aragorn!

540
00:51:11,193 --> 00:51:14,238
I'm to be sent with the women
into the caves.

541
00:51:14,405 --> 00:51:16,073
That is an honorable charge.

542
00:51:16,240 --> 00:51:19,118
To mind the children, to find food
and bedding when the men return.

543
00:51:19,285 --> 00:51:20,995
What renown is there in that?

544
00:51:21,161 --> 00:51:24,873
My lady, a time may come for valor
without renown.

545
00:51:25,124 --> 00:51:27,918
Who then will your people look to
in the last defense?

546
00:51:28,085 --> 00:51:33,090
-Let me stand at your side.
-It is not in my power to command it.

547
00:51:33,382 --> 00:51:36,218
You do not command
the others to stay!

548
00:51:36,385 --> 00:51:40,139
They fight beside you because they
would not be parted from you.

549
00:51:41,307 --> 00:51:43,517
Because they love you.

550
00:51:50,608 --> 00:51:52,151
I'm sorry.

551
00:52:03,621 --> 00:52:05,497
[BABY CRYING]

552
00:52:29,063 --> 00:52:32,024
[MUTED SPEECH]

553
00:52:47,581 --> 00:52:50,959
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

554
00:52:58,050 --> 00:53:01,345
Farmers, farriers, stable boys.

555
00:53:02,429 --> 00:53:04,223
These are no soldiers.

556
00:53:06,475 --> 00:53:09,978
-Most have seen too many winters.
-Or too few.

557
00:53:13,899 --> 00:53:16,819
Look at them. They're frightened.

558
00:53:16,985 --> 00:53:18,445
I can see it in their eyes.

559
00:53:23,631 --> 00:53:25,453
[IN SINDARIN] (Boe a hyn...)

560
00:53:25,803 --> 00:53:27,555
(Neled herain...                            )

561
00:53:27,580 --> 00:53:28,946
(Neled herain... dan caer menig!)

562
00:53:30,675 --> 00:53:32,893
[IN SINDARIN] (Si beriathar hyn ammaeg na ned Edoras...)

563
00:53:32,918 --> 00:53:34,169
Aragorn.

564
00:53:34,303 --> 00:53:36,970
(Nedin dagor hen ú-'erir ortheri.)

565
00:53:37,887 --> 00:53:39,250
(Natha daged dhaer!)

566
00:53:39,383 --> 00:53:41,593
[IN ENGLISH]
Then I shall die as one of them!

567
00:53:48,016 --> 00:53:49,852
GIMLI:
Let him go, lad.

568
00:53:50,436 --> 00:53:52,354
Let him be.

569
00:53:53,856 --> 00:53:59,361
Every villager able to wield a sword
has been sent to the armoury.

570
00:54:03,615 --> 00:54:05,534
My lord?

571
00:54:07,578 --> 00:54:10,164
Who am I, Gamling?

572
00:54:13,542 --> 00:54:17,421
You are our king, sire.

573
00:54:20,424 --> 00:54:23,719
And do you trust your king?

574
00:54:25,220 --> 00:54:28,390
Your men, my lord...

575
00:54:28,557 --> 00:54:31,393
...will follow you to whatever end.

576
00:54:38,233 --> 00:54:40,152
To whatever end.

577
00:54:49,995 --> 00:54:53,582
Where is the horse and the rider?

578
00:54:53,749 --> 00:54:56,794
Where is the horn that was blowing?

579
00:54:58,295 --> 00:55:02,758
<i>They have passed like rain
on the mountains.</i>

580
00:55:03,759 --> 00:55:06,970
<i>Like wind in the meadow.</i>

581
00:55:10,641 --> 00:55:14,436
The days have gone down in the West...

582
00:55:15,103 --> 00:55:17,773
<i>...behind the hills...</i>

583
00:55:19,650 --> 00:55:21,276
<i>...into Shadow.</i>

584
00:55:29,743 --> 00:55:33,163
How did it come to this?

585
00:55:42,756 --> 00:55:45,592
[ENTS GROANING]

586
00:55:49,471 --> 00:55:51,098
Huh?

587
00:55:54,476 --> 00:55:56,311
It's been going for hours.

588
00:55:57,479 --> 00:55:59,898
They must have decided something
by now.

589
00:56:00,065 --> 00:56:04,152
TREEBEARD:
Decided? No.

590
00:56:04,319 --> 00:56:09,491
We only just finished saying...

591
00:56:10,659 --> 00:56:12,536
...good morning.

592
00:56:13,871 --> 00:56:17,082
But it's nighttime already.

593
00:56:17,249 --> 00:56:19,042
You can't take forever.

594
00:56:20,043 --> 00:56:22,129
Don't be hasty.

595
00:56:22,546 --> 00:56:24,965
We're running out of time!

596
00:56:28,010 --> 00:56:30,929
GUARD:
Move! Move to the outer wall.

597
00:56:48,488 --> 00:56:49,823
Give me your sword.

598
00:56:59,291 --> 00:57:00,500
What is your name?

599
00:57:01,043 --> 00:57:03,378
Haleth, son of Háma, my lord.

600
00:57:05,547 --> 00:57:08,175
The men are saying that
we will not live out the night.

601
00:57:10,135 --> 00:57:12,095
They say that it is hopeless.

602
00:57:29,905 --> 00:57:31,573
This is a good sword.

603
00:57:33,575 --> 00:57:35,911
Haleth, son of Háma...

604
00:57:40,248 --> 00:57:42,417
...there is always hope.

605
00:58:05,399 --> 00:58:08,777
We have trusted you this far.
You have not led us astray.

606
00:58:08,944 --> 00:58:10,487
Forgive me.

607
00:58:10,654 --> 00:58:12,114
I was wrong to despair.

608
00:58:15,283 --> 00:58:17,852
[IN SINDARIN] (Ú-moe edhored, Legolas.)

609
00:58:20,956 --> 00:58:24,126
We had time, I'd get this adjusted.

610
00:58:27,546 --> 00:58:29,631
It's a little tight across the chest.

611
00:58:32,259 --> 00:58:34,511
[HORN BLOWING]

612
00:58:35,804 --> 00:58:37,764
That is no Orc horn.

613
00:58:43,437 --> 00:58:45,272
Send for the king.

614
00:58:45,439 --> 00:58:49,026
-Open the gate!
GUARD: Open up the gate!

615
00:59:20,682 --> 00:59:22,350
How is this possible?

616
00:59:23,351 --> 00:59:27,022
I bring word from Elrond of Rivendell.

617
00:59:27,189 --> 00:59:30,400
An alliance once existed
between Elves and Men.

618
00:59:31,109 --> 00:59:35,363
Long ago we fought and died together.

619
00:59:37,616 --> 00:59:40,535
We come to honor that allegiance.

620
00:59:40,990 --> 00:59:43,243
Well met, Haldir!
(Mae govannen, Haldir!)

621
00:59:49,002 --> 00:59:50,921
[IN ENGLISH]
You are most welcome.

622
00:59:56,301 --> 01:00:00,097
We are proud to fight
alongside Men once more.

623
01:00:22,369 --> 01:00:26,248
[MARCHING FOOTSTEPS
APPROACHING]

624
01:00:26,581 --> 01:00:29,918
[INDISTINCT GRUNTING
AND GROWLING]

625
01:00:33,880 --> 01:00:37,134
GIMLI:
You could have picked a better spot.

626
01:00:41,972 --> 01:00:46,184
Well, lad, whatever luck you live by,
let's hope it lasts the night.

627
01:00:47,394 --> 01:00:49,354
[THUNDER ROLLS]

628
01:00:52,315 --> 01:00:54,109
Your friends are with you, Aragorn.

629
01:00:54,734 --> 01:00:57,237
Let's hope they last the night.

630
01:01:00,198 --> 01:01:03,076
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

631
01:01:32,189 --> 01:01:35,233
[MARCHING FOOTSTEPS
APPROACHING]

632
01:01:39,779 --> 01:01:41,448
[BABY CRYING]

633
01:01:57,214 --> 01:01:58,770
[IN SINDARIN] O, Children of Eru... (A Eruchîn...)

634
01:01:58,976 --> 01:02:01,073
...show them no mercy... (...ú-dano i faelas a hyn...)

635
01:02:01,945 --> 01:02:04,365
(an uben tanatha le faelas!)

636
01:02:08,475 --> 01:02:10,769
[ROARS]

637
01:02:38,672 --> 01:02:41,508
-What's happening out there?
-Shall I describe it to you?

638
01:02:42,759 --> 01:02:44,552
Or would you like me to find you a box?

639
01:02:47,597 --> 01:02:52,018
[URUK-HAI BATTLE CRIES]

640
01:03:23,987 --> 01:03:24,658
(Dartho!)

641
01:03:27,304 --> 01:03:29,306
[GROANS]

642
01:03:47,741 --> 01:03:49,576
So it begins.

643
01:03:55,484 --> 01:03:56,694
(Tangado a chadad!)

644
01:04:05,674 --> 01:04:08,022
[IN SINDARIN] (Faeg i-varv...dîn na lanc...)

645
01:04:08,047 --> 01:04:09,699
(...a nu ranc.)

646
01:04:09,727 --> 01:04:11,445
(Leithio i philinn!)

647
01:04:16,436 --> 01:04:17,771
Did they hit anything?

648
01:04:18,438 --> 01:04:20,440
Give them a volley.

649
01:04:20,607 --> 01:04:22,734
-Fire!
-Fire!

650
01:04:28,114 --> 01:04:31,576
Release arrows!
(Hado i philinn!)

651
01:04:38,458 --> 01:04:40,126
Send them to me! Come on!

652
01:04:59,749 --> 01:05:00,841
(Pendraith!)

653
01:05:00,939 --> 01:05:01,981
Good!

654
01:05:08,780 --> 01:05:11,783
[IN ENGLISH]
Swords! Swords!

655
01:05:49,863 --> 01:05:51,990
Legolas! Two already!

656
01:05:52,157 --> 01:05:54,284
[IN ENGLISH]
I'm on 17!

657
01:05:54,451 --> 01:05:57,036
I'll have no pointy-ear outscoring me!

658
01:06:03,835 --> 01:06:05,545
Nineteen!

659
01:06:27,108 --> 01:06:30,153
[ENTS GROANING]

660
01:06:31,529 --> 01:06:32,947
Merry.

661
01:06:37,368 --> 01:06:41,164
We have just agreed.

662
01:06:51,174 --> 01:06:52,634
Yes?

663
01:06:54,135 --> 01:06:58,306
I have told your names to the Entmoot...

664
01:06:59,432 --> 01:07:02,685
...and we have agreed...

665
01:07:03,144 --> 01:07:07,190
...you are not Orcs.

666
01:07:08,942 --> 01:07:11,069
Well, that's good news.

667
01:07:11,236 --> 01:07:15,365
And what about Saruman?
Have you come to a decision about him?

668
01:07:15,990 --> 01:07:19,786
Now, don't be hasty, Master Meriadoc.

669
01:07:19,953 --> 01:07:21,496
Hasty?

670
01:07:22,288 --> 01:07:24,165
Our friends are out there.

671
01:07:24,332 --> 01:07:28,503
They need our help. They cannot
fight this war on their own.

672
01:07:28,836 --> 01:07:31,130
War? Yes.

673
01:07:31,297 --> 01:07:33,174
It affects us all.

674
01:07:33,341 --> 01:07:36,344
Tree, root and twig.

675
01:07:37,220 --> 01:07:41,266
But you must understand, young Hobbit...

676
01:07:41,474 --> 01:07:43,393
...it takes a long time...

677
01:07:43,560 --> 01:07:48,481
...to say anything in Old Entish...

678
01:07:48,648 --> 01:07:52,860
...and we never say anything...

679
01:07:53,027 --> 01:07:56,948
...unless it is worth taking...

680
01:07:57,115 --> 01:08:01,160
...a long time to say.

681
01:08:01,953 --> 01:08:05,248
Seventeen! Eighteen!

682
01:08:05,415 --> 01:08:06,499
Nineteen!

683
01:08:07,041 --> 01:08:08,918
Twenty!

684
01:08:09,085 --> 01:08:10,753
Twenty-one!

685
01:08:20,847 --> 01:08:21,889
Causeway!

686
01:08:21,914 --> 01:08:23,126
[IN SINDARIN] Causeway!
(Na fennas!)

687
01:08:23,151 --> 01:08:24,366
<i>Shoot continuously!
(Hado ribed!)</i>

688
01:08:24,862 --> 01:08:26,077
<i>Throw!
(Hado!)</i>

689
01:08:30,607 --> 01:08:32,984
Is this it?

690
01:08:33,151 --> 01:08:36,070
Is this all you can conjure, Saruman?

691
01:09:02,410 --> 01:09:03,877
(Togo han dad, Legolas!)

692
01:09:07,171 --> 01:09:08,243
(Dago hon!)

693
01:09:08,534 --> 01:09:09,315
(Dago hon!)

694
01:10:02,073 --> 01:10:03,449
Brace the gate!

695
01:10:21,759 --> 01:10:24,011
Hold them! Stand firm!

696
01:10:31,894 --> 01:10:33,229
Aragorn!

697
01:10:37,859 --> 01:10:39,068
Gimli!

698
01:10:45,324 --> 01:10:46,784
Hurl the arrows!
(Hado i philinn!)

699
01:10:49,816 --> 01:10:50,766
(Herio!)

700
01:11:27,825 --> 01:11:31,746
The Ents cannot hold back this storm.

701
01:11:32,538 --> 01:11:36,542
We must weather such things
as we have always done.

702
01:11:37,376 --> 01:11:39,462
How can that be your decision?!

703
01:11:40,129 --> 01:11:43,758
This is not our war.

704
01:11:44,050 --> 01:11:46,260
But you're part of this world!

705
01:11:50,389 --> 01:11:52,225
Aren't you?!

706
01:11:53,184 --> 01:11:55,895
[ENTS GRUMBLING]

707
01:11:56,312 --> 01:11:58,689
You must help. Please.

708
01:11:59,982 --> 01:12:02,735
You must do something.

709
01:12:03,027 --> 01:12:07,323
You are young and brave, Master Merry.

710
01:12:08,533 --> 01:12:12,245
But your part in this tale is over.

711
01:12:12,411 --> 01:12:14,664
Go back to your home.

712
01:12:24,674 --> 01:12:26,926
Maybe Treebeard's right.

713
01:12:27,093 --> 01:12:28,970
We don't belong here, Merry.

714
01:12:29,136 --> 01:12:31,430
It's too big for us.

715
01:12:31,597 --> 01:12:34,267
What can we do in the end?

716
01:12:36,561 --> 01:12:39,188
We've got the Shire.

717
01:12:39,730 --> 01:12:42,275
Maybe we should go home.

718
01:12:44,110 --> 01:12:47,321
The fires of Isengard will spread...

719
01:12:47,488 --> 01:12:52,410
...and the woods of Tuckborough
and Buckland will burn.

720
01:12:52,577 --> 01:12:54,161
And...

721
01:12:55,955 --> 01:12:59,041
And all that was once green and good
in this world will be gone.

722
01:13:02,587 --> 01:13:05,506
There won't be a Shire, Pippin.

723
01:13:25,026 --> 01:13:26,277
GAMLING:
Aragorn!

724
01:13:26,444 --> 01:13:28,821
Fall back to the Keep!

725
01:13:28,988 --> 01:13:32,074
Get your men out of there!

726
01:13:33,211 --> 01:13:34,757
[IN SINDARIN] (Nan Barad!)

727
01:13:39,568 --> 01:13:41,180
To the Keep! (Nan Barad!)

728
01:13:41,709 --> 01:13:43,377
Haldir!

729
01:13:47,506 --> 01:13:50,760
GIMLI: What are you doing?
What are you stopping for?

730
01:13:51,627 --> 01:13:53,123
[IN SINDARIN] To the Keep!
(Nan Barad!)

731
01:14:09,987 --> 01:14:11,197
Haldir!

732
01:14:53,906 --> 01:14:55,408
MAN:
Brace the gate!

733
01:14:57,618 --> 01:14:58,911
Hold them!

734
01:15:00,746 --> 01:15:04,125
To the gate. Draw your swords!

735
01:15:32,278 --> 01:15:34,196
Make way!

736
01:15:37,116 --> 01:15:38,826
We cannot hold much longer!

737
01:15:44,790 --> 01:15:48,377
THÉODEN: Hold them!
-How long do you need?

738
01:15:48,544 --> 01:15:51,130
As long as you can give me.

739
01:15:51,297 --> 01:15:52,965
Gimli!

740
01:15:54,425 --> 01:15:55,801
Timbers!

741
01:15:55,968 --> 01:15:57,928
MAN:
Brace the gate!

742
01:16:12,693 --> 01:16:14,403
Come on. We can take them.

743
01:16:15,237 --> 01:16:16,864
It's a long way.

744
01:16:22,119 --> 01:16:23,871
Toss me.

745
01:16:25,039 --> 01:16:26,874
-What?
-I cannot jump the distance!

746
01:16:27,041 --> 01:16:28,626
You'll have to toss me!

747
01:16:34,215 --> 01:16:35,508
Don't tell the Elf.

748
01:16:36,008 --> 01:16:37,802
Not a word.

749
01:16:53,025 --> 01:16:54,485
Shore up the door!

750
01:16:54,652 --> 01:16:56,737
MAN 1: Make way!
MAN 2: Follow me to the barricade.

751
01:16:56,904 --> 01:16:57,988
MAN 1:
Watch our backs!

752
01:17:02,118 --> 01:17:04,370
MAN 3: Throw another one over here!
-Higher!

753
01:17:54,295 --> 01:17:55,713
MAN 4:
Hold fast the gate!

754
01:17:59,925 --> 01:18:02,887
Gimli! Aragorn!
Get out of there!

755
01:18:07,600 --> 01:18:09,226
Aragorn!

756
01:18:42,635 --> 01:18:45,095
Pull everybody back.

757
01:18:45,471 --> 01:18:47,264
Pull them back.

758
01:18:47,806 --> 01:18:49,266
Fall back!

759
01:18:49,433 --> 01:18:51,936
Fall back!

760
01:18:53,103 --> 01:18:54,688
THÉODEN:
They have broken through!

761
01:18:54,855 --> 01:18:57,233
The castle is breached. Retreat!

762
01:18:57,399 --> 01:18:59,652
GAMLING: Fall back!
THÉODEN: Retreat!

763
01:18:59,818 --> 01:19:02,404
ARAGORN:
Hurry! Inside. Get them inside!

764
01:19:02,571 --> 01:19:04,823
THÉODEN:
Into the Keep!

765
01:19:16,293 --> 01:19:21,257
I will leave you at the western borders
of the forest.

766
01:19:21,423 --> 01:19:26,136
You can make your way north
to your homeland from there.

767
01:19:31,850 --> 01:19:33,143
Wait! Stop!

768
01:19:34,019 --> 01:19:35,521
Stop!

769
01:19:38,649 --> 01:19:40,359
Turn around.

770
01:19:41,277 --> 01:19:43,988
-Turn around. Take us south.
-South?

771
01:19:44,154 --> 01:19:49,159
But that will lead you past Isengard.

772
01:19:49,493 --> 01:19:52,204
Yes. Exactly.

773
01:19:52,371 --> 01:19:55,582
If we go south, we can slip
past Saruman unnoticed.

774
01:19:55,749 --> 01:19:58,419
The closer we are to danger,
the farther we are from harm.

775
01:19:58,585 --> 01:20:00,587
It's the last thing he'll expect.

776
01:20:03,215 --> 01:20:06,218
That doesn't make sense to me.

777
01:20:06,385 --> 01:20:07,553
But then...

778
01:20:07,720 --> 01:20:10,431
...you are very small.

779
01:20:10,889 --> 01:20:12,683
Perhaps you're right.

780
01:20:15,311 --> 01:20:16,854
South it is, then.

781
01:20:18,355 --> 01:20:21,692
Hold on, little Shirelings.

782
01:20:23,736 --> 01:20:26,488
I always like going south.

783
01:20:26,655 --> 01:20:30,951
Somehow it feels like going downhill.

784
01:20:31,577 --> 01:20:34,038
Are you mad? We'll be caught.

785
01:20:34,204 --> 01:20:36,123
No, we won't.

786
01:20:36,874 --> 01:20:39,126
Not this time.

787
01:20:45,758 --> 01:20:46,800
MAN:
Look!

788
01:20:48,427 --> 01:20:50,888
Osgiliath burns!

789
01:20:51,055 --> 01:20:52,473
Mordor has come.

790
01:20:53,599 --> 01:20:56,018
The Ring will not save Gondor.

791
01:20:57,353 --> 01:20:59,563
It has only the power to destroy.

792
01:21:00,439 --> 01:21:01,899
Please...

793
01:21:02,066 --> 01:21:03,692
...let me go.

794
01:21:04,735 --> 01:21:06,320
Hurry.

795
01:21:09,782 --> 01:21:11,200
FRODO:
Faramir!

796
01:21:11,367 --> 01:21:13,702
You must let me go!

797
01:21:14,286 --> 01:21:17,748
TREEBEARD:
And those little family of field mice...

798
01:21:17,915 --> 01:21:20,751
...that climb up sometimes,
and they tickle me awfully.

799
01:21:21,460 --> 01:21:24,797
They're always trying to get somewhere
where they...

800
01:21:25,214 --> 01:21:27,549
[GASPS]

801
01:21:35,974 --> 01:21:38,894
Many of these trees were my friends.

802
01:21:39,603 --> 01:21:44,233
Creatures I had known
from nut and acorn.

803
01:21:45,401 --> 01:21:46,610
I'm sorry, Treebeard.

804
01:21:46,777 --> 01:21:49,530
They had voices of their own.

805
01:21:51,782 --> 01:21:54,326
Saruman.

806
01:21:54,660 --> 01:21:57,746
A wizard should know better!

807
01:22:00,165 --> 01:22:03,085
[ROARING]

808
01:22:12,010 --> 01:22:15,681
There is no curse in Elvish...

809
01:22:15,848 --> 01:22:18,517
...Entish or the tongues of Men...

810
01:22:18,684 --> 01:22:21,019
...for this treachery.

811
01:22:22,438 --> 01:22:25,274
Look! The trees! They're moving!

812
01:22:29,987 --> 01:22:31,196
Where are they going?

813
01:22:31,697 --> 01:22:34,950
They have business with the Orcs.

814
01:22:35,409 --> 01:22:39,705
My business is with Isengard tonight...

815
01:22:39,872 --> 01:22:42,499
...with rock and stone.

816
01:22:42,875 --> 01:22:46,795
[GROANING AND FOOTSTEPS
APPROACHING]

817
01:23:06,398 --> 01:23:07,566
Yes.

818
01:23:08,650 --> 01:23:10,068
TREEBEARD:
Come, my friends.

819
01:23:11,403 --> 01:23:15,616
The Ents are going to war.

820
01:23:15,782 --> 01:23:17,576
It is likely...

821
01:23:17,743 --> 01:23:21,246
...that we go to our doom.

822
01:23:22,664 --> 01:23:25,125
Last march...

823
01:23:25,667 --> 01:23:27,711
...of the Ents.

824
01:24:15,801 --> 01:24:19,555
Faramir! Orcs have taken the eastern
shore. Their numbers are too great.

825
01:24:19,721 --> 01:24:21,807
By nightfall we will be overrun.

826
01:24:24,560 --> 01:24:26,019
Mr. Frodo?

827
01:24:26,311 --> 01:24:30,440
It's calling to him, Sam.
His Eye is almost on me.

828
01:24:30,607 --> 01:24:33,110
Hold on, Mr. Frodo.
You'll be all right.

829
01:24:35,612 --> 01:24:38,490
[MUTED SPEECH]

830
01:24:47,416 --> 01:24:48,834
Take them to my father.

831
01:24:50,377 --> 01:24:53,380
Tell him Faramir sends a mighty gift.

832
01:24:55,799 --> 01:24:58,844
A weapon that will change our fortunes
in this war.

833
01:25:00,012 --> 01:25:02,681
Do you want to know
what happened to Boromir?

834
01:25:03,348 --> 01:25:06,101
You want to know
why your brother died?

835
01:25:06,602 --> 01:25:10,355
He tried to take the Ring from Frodo
after swearing an oath to protect him!

836
01:25:10,522 --> 01:25:12,399
He tried to kill him!

837
01:25:12,566 --> 01:25:14,901
The Ring drove your brother mad!

838
01:25:15,694 --> 01:25:17,529
ITHILIEN RANGER:
Watch out!

839
01:25:25,203 --> 01:25:28,165
[RUMBLING]

840
01:25:28,457 --> 01:25:29,583
Mr. Frodo?

841
01:25:32,210 --> 01:25:34,046
They're here.

842
01:25:37,174 --> 01:25:39,635
They've come.

843
01:25:40,260 --> 01:25:41,887
[RINGWRAITH SCREECHING]

844
01:25:42,220 --> 01:25:44,097
Nazgûl!

845
01:25:44,306 --> 01:25:46,600
[ROARING]

846
01:26:06,244 --> 01:26:08,413
Stay here. Keep out of sight.

847
01:26:10,207 --> 01:26:12,417
Take cover!

848
01:26:29,768 --> 01:26:31,311
THÉODEN:
The fortress is taken.

849
01:26:32,104 --> 01:26:33,271
It is over.

850
01:26:33,438 --> 01:26:37,401
You said this fortress would never fall
while your men defend it.

851
01:26:37,567 --> 01:26:40,487
They still defend it.
They have died defending it.

852
01:26:43,240 --> 01:26:44,616
WOMAN 1:
They're breaking in!

853
01:26:47,285 --> 01:26:49,788
WOMAN 2:
They're past the door!

854
01:26:53,125 --> 01:26:57,254
Is there no other way for the women
and children to get out of the caves?

855
01:26:59,923 --> 01:27:01,842
Is there no other way?

856
01:27:03,427 --> 01:27:06,471
There is one passage.
It leads into the mountains.

857
01:27:07,139 --> 01:27:09,349
But they will not get far.
The Uruk-hai are too many.

858
01:27:14,229 --> 01:27:16,648
Tell the women and children
to make for the mountain pass.

859
01:27:16,815 --> 01:27:19,651
-And barricade the entrance!
-So much death.

860
01:27:21,820 --> 01:27:25,240
What can Men do
against such reckless hate?

861
01:27:29,911 --> 01:27:31,329
Ride out with me.

862
01:27:35,459 --> 01:27:37,085
Ride out and meet them.

863
01:27:37,836 --> 01:27:40,005
For death and glory.

864
01:27:40,172 --> 01:27:41,590
For Rohan.

865
01:27:43,091 --> 01:27:44,551
For your people.

866
01:27:45,302 --> 01:27:47,220
The sun is rising.

867
01:27:51,725 --> 01:27:54,728
GANDALF: <i> Look to my coming
at first light on the fifth day.</i>

868
01:27:54,895 --> 01:27:56,313
<i>At dawn...</i>

869
01:27:56,480 --> 01:27:58,190
<i>...look to the east.</i>

870
01:28:02,360 --> 01:28:04,029
Yes.

871
01:28:06,490 --> 01:28:08,158
Yes.

872
01:28:09,493 --> 01:28:11,870
The horn of Helm Hammerhand...

873
01:28:12,037 --> 01:28:14,873
...shall sound in the Deep...

874
01:28:15,290 --> 01:28:17,292
...one last time.

875
01:28:17,459 --> 01:28:18,960
Yes!

876
01:28:22,005 --> 01:28:25,801
Let this be the hour
when we draw swords together.

877
01:28:33,558 --> 01:28:34,893
Fell deeds, awake.

878
01:28:36,102 --> 01:28:37,229
Now for wrath...

879
01:28:37,395 --> 01:28:40,774
...now for ruin and a red dawn.

880
01:28:41,399 --> 01:28:44,444
[HORN BLOWS]

881
01:28:47,823 --> 01:28:50,075
Forth Eorlingas!

882
01:28:50,367 --> 01:28:52,744
[BATTLE CRIES]

883
01:29:33,243 --> 01:29:35,120
[HORSE NEIGHS]

884
01:29:37,873 --> 01:29:39,124
Gandalf.

885
01:29:46,381 --> 01:29:50,051
Théoden King stands alone.

886
01:29:50,635 --> 01:29:52,804
Not alone.

887
01:29:53,221 --> 01:29:54,347
Rohirrim!

888
01:30:00,270 --> 01:30:01,438
Éomer.

889
01:30:01,605 --> 01:30:04,149
To the king!

890
01:31:21,726 --> 01:31:23,520
Yes!

891
01:31:24,062 --> 01:31:25,271
[GRUNTS]

892
01:31:27,232 --> 01:31:29,567
[ENTS ROARING]

893
01:31:32,654 --> 01:31:35,949
TREEBEARD:
A hit. A fine hit.

894
01:31:36,116 --> 01:31:37,158
[TREEBEARD GRUNTS]

895
01:32:00,640 --> 01:32:03,101
TREEBEARD:
Break the dam!

896
01:32:03,268 --> 01:32:06,730
Release the river!

897
01:32:34,049 --> 01:32:36,801
Pippin! Hold on!

898
01:32:42,057 --> 01:32:44,976
Hold on, little Hobbits.

899
01:33:26,351 --> 01:33:28,353
What are you doing?

900
01:33:36,945 --> 01:33:38,530
Where are you going?

901
01:33:39,697 --> 01:33:43,910
[RUMBLING]

902
01:34:16,985 --> 01:34:18,945
[ROARING]

903
01:34:28,037 --> 01:34:29,289
[YELLS]

904
01:34:36,671 --> 01:34:38,006
It's me.

905
01:34:40,508 --> 01:34:42,719
It's your Sam.

906
01:34:47,056 --> 01:34:49,684
Don't you know your Sam?

907
01:34:58,109 --> 01:34:59,527
[PANTING]

908
01:34:59,694 --> 01:35:01,237
[SWORD CLANGS]

909
01:35:07,410 --> 01:35:10,788
I can't do this, Sam.

910
01:35:11,664 --> 01:35:13,666
I know.

911
01:35:14,667 --> 01:35:17,045
It's all wrong.

912
01:35:17,795 --> 01:35:19,797
By rights, we shouldn't even be here.

913
01:35:27,222 --> 01:35:29,307
But we are.

914
01:35:35,730 --> 01:35:38,775
It's like in the great stories, Mr. Frodo.

915
01:35:38,942 --> 01:35:41,319
The ones that really mattered.

916
01:35:42,362 --> 01:35:45,365
Full of darkness and danger they were.

917
01:35:45,531 --> 01:35:48,493
And sometimes you didn't want
to know the end...

918
01:35:48,660 --> 01:35:51,621
...because how could the end be happy?

919
01:35:54,165 --> 01:35:56,376
<i>How could the world go back
to the way it was...</i>

920
01:35:56,542 --> 01:36:00,046
<i>...when so much bad had happened?</i>

921
01:36:00,880 --> 01:36:02,799
Victory!

922
01:36:02,966 --> 01:36:04,509
We have victory!

923
01:36:04,676 --> 01:36:08,638
SAM: <i> But in the end,
it's only a passing thing...</i>

924
01:36:08,805 --> 01:36:10,139
<i>...this shadow.</i>

925
01:36:10,306 --> 01:36:12,684
<i>Even darkness must pass.</i>

926
01:36:12,850 --> 01:36:15,561
<i>A new day will come.</i>

927
01:36:15,728 --> 01:36:19,691
<i>And when the sun shines,
it will shine out the clearer.</i>

928
01:36:21,609 --> 01:36:23,987
<i>Those were the stories
that stayed with you...</i>

929
01:36:24,153 --> 01:36:25,905
<i>...that meant something.</i>

930
01:36:26,072 --> 01:36:28,658
<i>Even if you were too small
to understand why.</i>

931
01:36:30,034 --> 01:36:33,871
<i>But I think, Mr. Frodo, I do understand.</i>

932
01:36:34,038 --> 01:36:35,623
<i>I know now.</i>

933
01:36:36,457 --> 01:36:38,668
Folk in those stories...

934
01:36:38,835 --> 01:36:42,964
...had lots of chances of turning back,
only they didn't.

935
01:36:43,131 --> 01:36:45,383
They kept going...

936
01:36:46,050 --> 01:36:49,304
...because they were holding
on to something.

937
01:36:50,888 --> 01:36:53,224
What are we holding on to, Sam?

938
01:37:05,153 --> 01:37:09,073
That there's some good
in this world, Mr. Frodo.

939
01:37:09,365 --> 01:37:11,993
And it's worth fighting for.

940
01:37:38,895 --> 01:37:43,191
I think at last we understand one another,
Frodo Baggins.

941
01:37:43,941 --> 01:37:47,904
You know the laws of our country,
the laws of your father.

942
01:37:48,071 --> 01:37:50,281
If you let them go,
your life will be forfeit.

943
01:37:54,619 --> 01:37:56,037
Then it is forfeit.

944
01:37:58,790 --> 01:38:00,583
Release them.

945
01:38:09,342 --> 01:38:12,053
[HOOVES BEATING]

946
01:38:12,637 --> 01:38:14,680
ÉOMER:
Stay out of the forest!

947
01:38:14,847 --> 01:38:16,641
Keep away from the trees!

948
01:38:39,872 --> 01:38:43,960
[SCREAMING AND YELLING]

949
01:39:07,483 --> 01:39:09,277
Final count...

950
01:39:09,444 --> 01:39:12,363
-...42.
-Forty-two?

951
01:39:12,530 --> 01:39:18,578
Oh, that's not bad for a pointy-eared
Elvish princeling.

952
01:39:19,370 --> 01:39:23,040
I myself am sitting pretty on 43.

953
01:39:27,170 --> 01:39:30,465
-Forty-three.
-He was already dead.

954
01:39:31,215 --> 01:39:33,718
-He was twitching.
-He was twitching...

955
01:39:33,885 --> 01:39:38,514
...because he's got my ax
embedded in his nervous system!

956
01:39:40,808 --> 01:39:45,521
MERRY: He doesn't look happy, does he?
PIPPIN: Not too happy at all, Merry.

957
01:39:45,771 --> 01:39:49,317
Still, I suppose the view
would be quite nice from up there.

958
01:39:49,484 --> 01:39:52,445
Oh, yes. It's a quality establishment.

959
01:39:52,612 --> 01:39:55,448
I hear the staff are very good.

960
01:40:01,120 --> 01:40:03,498
-What are you doing?
-Nothing.

961
01:40:03,664 --> 01:40:07,919
-The world's back to normal, that's all.
-No, it isn't.

962
01:40:08,085 --> 01:40:09,337
I'm starving.

963
01:40:09,504 --> 01:40:12,590
Good luck trying to find something
decent around here.

964
01:40:12,757 --> 01:40:15,843
Probably dead rats and moldy bread.

965
01:40:39,784 --> 01:40:42,203
Saruman's storeroom!

966
01:40:44,539 --> 01:40:47,291
I don't believe it.

967
01:40:47,458 --> 01:40:49,502
It can't be.

968
01:40:50,127 --> 01:40:53,005
-It is!
-Longbottom Leaf.

969
01:40:54,298 --> 01:40:56,634
The finest pipe-weed in South Farthing.

970
01:40:56,968 --> 01:41:00,096
It's perfect. One barrel each.

971
01:41:00,263 --> 01:41:01,389
Wait.

972
01:41:02,139 --> 01:41:03,349
Do you think we should share it
with Treebeard?

973
01:41:03,516 --> 01:41:05,059
Share it?

974
01:41:06,894 --> 01:41:09,313
No. No.

975
01:41:10,815 --> 01:41:12,149
Dead plant and all that.

976
01:41:12,567 --> 01:41:14,735
Don't think he'd understand.

977
01:41:15,987 --> 01:41:18,197
Could be a distant relative.

978
01:41:18,990 --> 01:41:21,492
I get it.

979
01:41:21,659 --> 01:41:24,495
Don't be hasty.

980
01:41:25,580 --> 01:41:27,331
Exactly.

981
01:41:28,416 --> 01:41:30,668
Bar-hrum.

982
01:41:32,503 --> 01:41:34,505
[HOBBITS LAUGHING]

983
01:41:56,319 --> 01:41:57,612
This is the old sewer.

984
01:41:57,778 --> 01:42:00,906
Runs right under the river
through to the edge of the city.

985
01:42:01,073 --> 01:42:02,825
You'll find cover in the woods there.

986
01:42:03,868 --> 01:42:06,370
Captain Faramir...

987
01:42:06,996 --> 01:42:08,831
...you have shown your quality, sir.

988
01:42:11,334 --> 01:42:12,627
The very highest.

989
01:42:13,127 --> 01:42:15,755
The Shire must truly be a great realm,
Master Gamgee...

990
01:42:15,921 --> 01:42:18,883
...where gardeners are held in high honor.

991
01:42:20,051 --> 01:42:22,053
What road will you take
once you reach the woods?

992
01:42:22,637 --> 01:42:24,221
Gollum says there's a path...

993
01:42:24,388 --> 01:42:28,309
...near Minas Morgul
that climbs up into the mountains.

994
01:42:28,768 --> 01:42:30,519
Cirith Ungol?

995
01:42:34,065 --> 01:42:36,609
-Is that its name?
-No.

996
01:42:36,776 --> 01:42:38,444
No!

997
01:42:39,278 --> 01:42:42,281
-Yes.
-Frodo...

998
01:42:42,657 --> 01:42:46,202
...they say a dark terror dwells
in the passes above Minas Morgul.

999
01:42:47,078 --> 01:42:49,622
-You cannot go that way.
SMÉAGOL: It is the only way.

1000
01:42:49,955 --> 01:42:56,253
Master says we must go to Mordor,
so we must try.

1001
01:42:57,755 --> 01:42:59,548
I must.

1002
01:43:03,094 --> 01:43:06,681
Go, Frodo.
Go with the goodwill of all Men.

1003
01:43:06,847 --> 01:43:08,891
Thank you.

1004
01:43:20,695 --> 01:43:24,824
May death find you quickly
if you bring them to harm.

1005
01:43:37,294 --> 01:43:38,838
SAM:
Come on, keep up.

1006
01:43:42,299 --> 01:43:45,094
Mr. Frodo didn't mean for them Rangers
to hurt you.

1007
01:43:45,720 --> 01:43:47,555
You know that, don't you?

1008
01:43:48,347 --> 01:43:49,932
He was trying to save you, see?

1009
01:43:50,433 --> 01:43:51,976
Save me?

1010
01:43:52,309 --> 01:43:54,478
So there's no hard feelings.

1011
01:43:54,645 --> 01:43:59,775
-Forgive and forget.
-No, no, no hard feelings.

1012
01:43:59,942 --> 01:44:02,570
Gollum, Gollum.

1013
01:44:03,612 --> 01:44:05,364
Nice master.

1014
01:44:06,449 --> 01:44:09,285
-Nice Hobbits.
SAM: Very decent of you.

1015
01:44:09,452 --> 01:44:11,746
Very decent, indeed, Gollum.

1016
01:44:17,251 --> 01:44:22,465
Sauron's wrath will be terrible,
his retribution swift.

1017
01:44:24,258 --> 01:44:27,595
[RUMBLING]

1018
01:44:29,597 --> 01:44:32,600
GANDALF:
The battle for Helm's Deep is over.

1019
01:44:33,267 --> 01:44:36,812
The battle for Middle-earth
is about to begin.

1020
01:44:41,942 --> 01:44:45,362
All our hopes now lie
with two little Hobbits...

1021
01:44:46,363 --> 01:44:49,575
<i>...somewhere in the wilderness.</i>

1022
01:44:52,870 --> 01:44:56,290
I wonder if we'll ever be
put into songs or tales.

1023
01:44:56,457 --> 01:44:57,833
What?

1024
01:44:58,000 --> 01:45:01,962
I wonder if people will ever say,
"Let's hear about Frodo and the Ring."

1025
01:45:02,129 --> 01:45:05,382
And they'll say,
"Yes! That's one of my favorite stories.”

1026
01:45:05,549 --> 01:45:08,511
"Frodo was really courageous,
wasn't he, Dad?"

1027
01:45:08,677 --> 01:45:10,346
"Yes, my boy.

1028
01:45:10,513 --> 01:45:14,308
The most famousest of Hobbits.
And that's saying a lot."

1029
01:45:14,475 --> 01:45:17,019
Well, you've left out
one of the chief characters:

1030
01:45:17,186 --> 01:45:19,063
"Samwise the Brave."

1031
01:45:19,230 --> 01:45:21,982
I want to hear more about Sam.

1032
01:45:26,278 --> 01:45:29,281
Frodo wouldn't have got far
without Sam.

1033
01:45:30,616 --> 01:45:34,662
Now, Mr. Frodo, you shouldn't make fun.
I was being serious.

1034
01:45:35,746 --> 01:45:37,122
So was I.

1035
01:45:46,006 --> 01:45:48,717
"Samwise the Brave."

1036
01:45:52,972 --> 01:45:54,306
FRODO:
Sméagol?

1037
01:45:54,473 --> 01:45:57,393
SAM: We're not going to wait for you.
Come on.

1038
01:45:57,560 --> 01:45:59,478
Master.

1039
01:45:59,645 --> 01:46:02,606
Master looks after us.

1040
01:46:03,399 --> 01:46:06,193
Master wouldn't hurt us.

1041
01:46:06,360 --> 01:46:08,821
GOLLUM:
Master broke his promise.

1042
01:46:08,988 --> 01:46:11,156
SMÉAGOL:
Don't ask Sméagol.

1043
01:46:11,323 --> 01:46:14,535
Poor, poor Sméagol.

1044
01:46:14,702 --> 01:46:17,538
Master betrayed us.

1045
01:46:17,705 --> 01:46:20,791
Wicked. Tricksy. False.

1046
01:46:20,958 --> 01:46:24,879
We ought to wring
his filthy little neck.

1047
01:46:25,045 --> 01:46:27,798
Kill him! Kill him!

1048
01:46:27,965 --> 01:46:29,466
Kill them both!

1049
01:46:29,633 --> 01:46:33,262
And then we take the precious...

1050
01:46:33,429 --> 01:46:36,974
...and we be the master!

1051
01:46:37,641 --> 01:46:40,311
But the fat Hobbit, he knows.

1052
01:46:40,477 --> 01:46:43,147
Eyes always watching.

1053
01:46:43,314 --> 01:46:46,859
Then we stabs them out.

1054
01:46:47,026 --> 01:46:51,530
Put out his eyeses
and make him crawl.

1055
01:46:51,697 --> 01:46:55,159
Yes. Yes. Yes.

1056
01:46:55,326 --> 01:46:58,037
Kill them both.

1057
01:46:58,203 --> 01:47:00,706
Yes. No! No!

1058
01:47:00,873 --> 01:47:04,585
It's too risky. It's too risky.

1059
01:47:05,294 --> 01:47:07,880
SAM:
Where is he? Where has he gone?

1060
01:47:08,047 --> 01:47:10,674
-Hey, Gollum! Where are you?
FRODO: Sméagol?

1061
01:47:10,841 --> 01:47:16,221
We could let her do it.

1062
01:47:17,181 --> 01:47:21,352
Yes. She could do it.

1063
01:47:21,518 --> 01:47:26,065
Yes, precious, she could.

1064
01:47:26,231 --> 01:47:32,279
And then we takes it
once they're dead.

1065
01:47:33,197 --> 01:47:34,949
Once they're dead.

1066
01:47:35,115 --> 01:47:37,117
Shh.

1067
01:47:40,454 --> 01:47:44,166
Come on, Hobbits. Long ways to go yet.

1068
01:47:44,333 --> 01:47:46,377
Sméagol will show you the way.

1069
01:47:46,543 --> 01:47:48,796
Follow me.

1070
01:48:07,231 --> 01:48:10,150
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

